text.section:
A general court-martial may impose one or more of the following penalties:
except as provided in subsection (d) of this section, a fine not exceeding $200;
forfeiture of pay and allowances;
reprimand;
dismissal or dishonorable discharge from the service;
reduction of noncommissioned officers to the ranks; or
confinement, in lieu of a fine, not to exceed 1 day for each dollar of fine authorized.

A summary court-martial may impose the following penalties:
a fine not exceeding $25 for a single offense;
reduction of noncommissioned officer to the ranks;
forfeiture of pay and allowances; or
confinement, in lieu of a fine, not to exceed 1 day for each dollar of fine authorized.
